        <section class="subject" id="what-i-do">
          <h3>What I do</h3>
          <p>
            I’m a <strong>software developer and consultant</strong>, specializing in modern <em>JavaScript, React, Node.js, and TypeScript</em>. I help companies build reliable, scalable applications while also mentoring their teams.
          </p>

          <p>
            A big part of my work is not just writing code, but making sure the people I work with feel <em>confident, supported, and able to grow</em>. I love simplifying complex technical concepts and turning them into something approachable and useful.
          </p>

          <img src="/assets/images/norge_2025.webp" alt="">

          <p>
            Alongside my development work, I am also an <strong>independent healthcare specialist</strong> <em>coaching, and supporting</em> young people with <strong>autism and ADHD</strong>. I teach subjects like computer science, game development, and fixing and making your own electronics, but more importantly, I create a safe space for <em>curiosity, creativity, and self-confidence</em>. For me, it’s not just about skills, it’s about helping these young people feel seen, capable, and empowered to explore their passions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="subject" id="development">
          <h3>Software Development</h3>
          <p>
            If you’re looking for a <strong>reliable developer</strong> to bring your project to life or take your existing product to the next level,
            <a href="/#contact">get in contact with me today</a> and let’s build something great together.
          </p>

          <p>
            I provide end-to-end web development services, specialising in <strong>JavaScript / TypeScript</strong>, with a strong focus on <strong>Node.js and React</strong>. I work both on the front end and back end, bringing together scalable, robust server-side architectures and high-quality, responsive user interfaces. My work tends to emphasize <em>performance, maintainability, and clean architecture</em>.
          </p>

          <p>
            Ask me to help you build web applications, ensure good user experience, create solid front-end frameworks, and ensure everything works together. From the server, through the API, to the client-side logic and UI interactions.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also take on consulting roles: helping clients decide whether certain technologies suit their project, architecting systems, and giving advice on scaling.
          </p>

          <p>
            I’m comfortable working on new builds (from scratch), as well as improving or iterating on existing codebases. Common tasks include building applications, making APIs, integrating with third-party services, and making sure things are reliable and secure.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="subject">
          <h3>Healthcare Specialist</h3>

          <p>
            I’m passionate about <strong>supporting young people with autism</strong> by <em>helping them discover their strengths and build confidence through technology</em>. Many of them have a natural curiosity for computers, coding, and electronics, and I create a safe, encouraging environment where they can explore those interests at their own pace. My goal is not only to teach technical skills but also to <em>nurture creativity, problem-solving, and self-expression</em>.
          </p>

          <p>
            I coach and mentor them in a wide range of IT and computer-related subjects, including <strong>programming, game development, building electronics and soldering</strong>. Whether we’re working on a small coding project, creating a game from scratch, or learning how to assemble hardware, I focus on breaking concepts down into <em>manageable steps, celebrating progress, and making the learning experience fun and accessible</em>.
          </p>

          <img src="/assets/images/wall-b_003.webp" alt="">

          <p>
            What matters most to me is helping each individual achieve their personal goals. Some want to learn coding for a future career, others want to build cool projects they can share with others, and some simply enjoy the process of experimenting with technology. <strong>I adapt my approach to each person</strong>, giving them the guidance, tools, and encouragement they need to succeed.
          </p>

          <p>
            Through this work, I aim to show young people with autism that <strong>they can thrive</strong>, building skills that open doors, spark curiosity, and give them the confidence to pursue their passions.
          </p>

          <p>
            If your organisation is looking for someone to support students in achieving their IT related goals; feel free to <a href="/#contact">reach out to me through email</a>. I do this on an independent basis, for hire.
          </p>
        </section>

