            From my parents’ attic, with a painfully slow internet connection, I taught myself how to build websites and backend systems. That curiosity eventually led me to pursue a bachelor’s degree in computer science while working part-time at a local web development company.
          </p>

          <p>
            Since then, I’ve worked with a lot of different companies and projects, learning lots about technology and mostly about myself. Along the way, I started blogging to process and share what I was learning. While I don’t write as often these days, I still enjoy sharing ideas, sometimes on my blog, sometimes over at <a target="_blank" href="https://sauce.gaya.pizza">sauce.gaya.pizza</a>.
          </p>

          <p>
            I also <strong>speak at events and conferences</strong> from time to time about what I learned. Though, like writing, not as often as I used to, but still open to it.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Apart from development and programming I like to take enough time off to enjoy life <em>away from the desk</em>.
          </p>
          
